      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just the sheer scale of it. people around me are all pushing for more, more papers, more prestige, more \"grit.\" but i look at the mountain of work ahead and i just feel nothing. no drive, no passion, just this void. it's like i've hit a wall that isn't meant to be climbed. i've spent everything i had on this path and now that it's failing, i don't even know who is left. i just want everything to stop. i wish i could just opt out of the struggle entirely. it feels like the only way to truly find relief is to just... stop existing.",
