      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know people say they care, but it feels like they only care about the version of me that was successful. the \"academic\" version. if i tell them how lost i actually am, they'll just see a failure. it feels like i'm performing a role that i'm no longer capable of playing. \n\neveryone is always talking about \"resilience\" like it's some infinite resource you can just tap into, but i'm empty. i've been trying to \"find a way out\" through therapy and talking and work, but nothing changes. it's just a cycle of more pressure, more failure, more exhaustion. at some point, doesn't it just become a logical conclusion that the struggle isn't worth the cost anymore? like, why keep fighting a battle that's already been lost?",
